21/07/2004
NEW YORK, United States -- During a meeting with members of the US business community in New York, Romanian Prime Minister Adrian Nastase pledged to intensify efforts to create a favourable investment climate in his country. During a working luncheon Monday (19 July) with US representatives of the Business Council for International Understanding, Nastase pledged that Bucharest would step up the pace of economic reforms to develop an attractive business environment as quickly as possible. On Tuesday, Nastase served as chairman of a UN Security Council session on stabilisation; Romania is the current holder of the Council's rotating presidency. On Wednesday, Nastase meets with President George W. Bush in Washington. (Rompres, UN Web site - 20/07/04)
